config.name: app_approval
config.description: If true the status of a new app is PENDING so that an administrator has to manually activate the app

config.name: app_consumer
config.description: The max amount of apps a consumer can register

config.name: authorization_url
config.description: Url where the user can authorize for the OAuth2 flow

config.name: consumer_subscription
config.description: The max amount of subscriptions a consumer can add

config.name: info_title
config.description: The title of the application

config.name: info_description
config.description: A short description of the application. CommonMark syntax MAY be used for rich text representation

config.name: info_tos
config.description: A URL to the Terms of Service for the API. MUST be in the format of a URL

config.name: info_contact_name
config.description: The identifying name of the contact person/organization

config.name: info_contact_url
config.description: The URL pointing to the contact information. MUST be in the format of a URL

config.name: info_contact_email
config.description: The email address of the contact person/organization. MUST be in the format of an email address

config.name: info_license_name
config.description: The license name used for the API

config.name: info_license_url
config.description: A URL to the license used for the API. MUST be in the format of a URL

config.name: mail_register_subject
config.description: Subject of the activation mail

config.name: mail_register_body
config.description: Body of the activation mail
config.value:
Hello {name},

you have successful registered at Fusio.
To activate you account please visit the following link:
{apps_url}/developer/register/activate/{token}

config.name: mail_pw_reset_subject
config.description: Subject of the password reset mail

config.name: mail_pw_reset_body
config.description: Body of the password reset mail
config.value:
Hello {name},

you have requested to reset your password.
To set a new password please visit the following link:
{apps_url}/developer/password/confirm/{token}

Please ignore this email if you have not requested a password reset.

config.name: mail_points_subject
config.description: Subject of the points threshold mail

config.name: mail_points_body
config.description: Body of the points threshold mail
config.value:
Hello {name},

your account has reached the configured threshold of {points} points.
If your account reaches 0 points your are not longer able to invoke specific endpoints.
To prevent this please go to the developer portal to purchase new points:
{apps_url}/developer

config.name: recaptcha_key
config.description: ReCaptcha key

config.name: recaptcha_secret
config.description: ReCaptcha secret

config.name: payment_stripe_secret
config.description: The stripe webhook secret which is needed to verify a webhook request

config.name: payment_stripe_portal_configuration
config.description: The stripe portal configuration id

config.name: payment_currency
config.description: The three-character ISO-4217 currency code which is used to process payments

config.name: role_default
config.description: Default role which a user gets assigned on registration

config.name: points_default
config.description: The default amount of points which a user receives if he registers

config.name: points_threshold
config.description: If a user goes below this points threshold we send an information to the user

config.name: system_mailer
config.description: Optional the name of an SMTP connection which is used as mailer, by default the system uses the connection configured through the APP_MAILER environment variable

config.name: system_dispatcher
config.description: Optional the name of an HTTP or Message-Queue connection which is used to dispatch events. By default the system uses simply cron and an internal table to dispatch such events, for better performance you can provide a Message-Queue connection and Fusio will only dispatch the event to the queue, then your worker must execute the actual webhook HTTP request

config.name: user_pw_length
config.description: Minimal required password length

config.name: user_approval
config.description: Whether the user needs to activate the account through an email
